      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i was wondering about the actual \"why\" behind it. like, is it just about the big words, or is there something about the actual dialect/logic in sample B that makes it \"lesser\"? i've heard some linguists say that certain dialects are just more direct or have different rules for being precise. do you think an academic reviewer might subconsciously associate the way Sample B is written with a lower level of intelligence or something?",
